  "market_context": "Intraday session after London/New York overlap; price had swept prior lows, formed a reversal candle with large wick, then showed change in state of delivery. Analyst used 15m for HTF bias and 1m for entry execution.",
  "key_observation": "A candle-2 closure reversal occurred on the 1-minute chart with a large wick, confirmed by SMT divergence and change in state of delivery; the analyst waited for the next candle’s open to enter the continuation move higher.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified a 15-minute candle-2 closure reversal with large wick but deemed it too late to enter during that candle.",
    "Step 2: Waited for the new 1-minute candle open as the preferred entry timing, per fractal model rules.",
    "Step 3: Observed price forming a shallow opposing run (small wick) into a fair value gap, supporting expansion lower initially, then reversed.",
    "Step 4: Confirmed change in state of delivery via closure through prior down-close candles and noted SMT divergence between ES and correlated assets.",
    "Step 5: Marked the previous candle’s low as the POI and anticipated a reversal/continuation higher from that level on the new candle.",
    "Step 6: Entered long at the open of the new higher-time-frame candle after confirming protected swing formation and small opposing wick."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade executed long at new candle open, targeting expansion into prior highs; price expanded higher as anticipated.",
  "lessons": "Never trade late into a reversal candle—even with valid structure—wait for the new candle open. Small opposing wicks + change in state of delivery + SMT confirmation provide high-probability continuation entries.",
